api_list.name: createNewConection
api_list.description: Create new connection

optional_parameters.name: timeout1xx
optional_parameters.description: Time(sec) before aborting if connection is not made (min: 1, max: 20)

optional_parameters.name: thirdPartyControlEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Applies to calls sent TO this connection.

optional_parameters.name: sipCompactHeadersEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Defaults to true

optional_parameters.name: aniOverrideType
optional_parameters.description: Specifies when we apply your ani_override setting. Only applies when ani_override is not blank.

optional_parameters.name: active
optional_parameters.description: Defaults to true

optional_parameters.name: aniOverride
optional_parameters.description: Set a phone number as the ani_override value to override caller id number on outbound calls

optional_parameters.name: privacyZoneEnabled
optional_parameters.description: By default, Telnyx does not send caller-id information when the caller has chosen to hide this information. When this option is enabled, Telnyx will send the SIP header Privacy:id plus the caller-id information so that the receiver side can choose when to hide it.

optional_parameters.name: timeout2xx
optional_parameters.description: Time(sec) before aborting if call is unanswered (min: 1, max: 600)

optional_parameters.name: defaultSecondaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default secondary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: encodeContactHeaderEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Encode the SIP contact header sent by Telnyx to avoid issues for NAT or ALG scenarios

optional_parameters.name: instantRingbackEnabled
optional_parameters.description: When set, ringback will not wait for indication before sending ringback tone to calling party.

optional_parameters.name: outboundLocalization
optional_parameters.description: A 2-character country code specifying the country whose national dialing rules should be used. For example, if set to `US` then any US number can be dialed without preprending +1 to the number. When left blank, Telnyx will try US and GB dialing rules, in that order, by default.

optional_parameters.name: anchorsiteOverride
optional_parameters.description: "Latency" directs Telnyx to route media through the site with the lowest round-trip time to the user's connection. Telnyx calculates this time using ICMP ping messages. This can be disabled by specifying a site to handle all media.

optional_parameters.name: defaultRoutingMethod
optional_parameters.description: Default routing method to be used when a number is associated with the connection.

optional_parameters.name: dnisNumberFormat
optional_parameters.description: E.164 = 0, Strip-1 = 1, Strip-2 = 2

optional_parameters.name: aniNumberFormat
optional_parameters.description: This setting allows you to set the format with which the caller's number (ANI) is sent for inbound phone calls.

optional_parameters.name: outboundGenerateRingbackTone
optional_parameters.description: Generate ringback tone through 183 session progress message with early media

optional_parameters.name: transportProtocol
optional_parameters.description: One of UDP, TLS, or TCP. Applies only to connections with IP authentication or FQDN authentication.

optional_parameters.name: dtmfType
optional_parameters.description: Sets the type of DTMF digits sent from Telnyx to this Connection. Note that DTMF digits sent to Telnyx will be accepted in all formats.

optional_parameters.name: inboundGenerateRingbackTone
optional_parameters.description: Generate ringback tone through 183 session progress message with early media

optional_parameters.name: defaultTertiaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default tertiary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: defaultPrimaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default primary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: t38ReinviteSource
optional_parameters.description: This setting only affects connections with Fax-type Outbound Profiles. The setting dictates whether or not Telnyx sends a t.38 reinvite. By default, Telnyx will send the re-invite. If set to `customer`, the caller is expected to send the t.38 reinvite.

optional_parameters.name: prackEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Enable PRACK messages as defined in RFC3262

optional_parameters.name: encryptedMedia
optional_parameters.description: Enable use of SRTP or ZRTP for encryption. Valid values are those listed or null. Cannot be set to non-null if the transport_portocol is TLS.

optional_parameters.name: isupHeadersEnabled
optional_parameters.description: When set, inbound phone calls will receive ISUP parameters via SIP headers. (Only when available and only when using TCP or TLS transport.) Defaults to false.

optional_parameters.name: codecs
optional_parameters.description: Defines the list of codecs that Telnyx will send for inbound calls to a specific number on your portal account, in priority order. This only works when the Connection the number is assigned to uses Media Handling mode: default. OPUS and H.264 codecs are available only when using TCP or TLS transport for SIP

api_list.name: setConnectionFQDNAuth
api_list.description: Sets the connection given by connectionId to use FQDN-based authentication. This will remove any other authentication type set for the connection. Please note that domains themselves are not added through this endpoint.

required_parameters.description: Username that will be sent when using the connection. Must be globally unique. Case-insensitive.

required_parameters.name: connectionPassword
required_parameters.description: Password that will be sent when using the connection. Must be at least 8 characters or more in length.

optional_parameters.name: ipAuthenticationMethod
optional_parameters.description: The method of authentication to use if this FQDN auth strategy uses IP-based outbound. Defaults to "tech-prefix". Has no effect if this auth strategy uses credentials for outbound authentication.

optional_parameters.name: fqdnOutboundAuthentication
optional_parameters.description: The method of authentication to use for outbound calls on this authentication strategy. Defaults to "credential-authentication".

api_list.name: setConnectionIpAuth
api_list.description: Sets the connection given by connectionId to use IP-based authentication. This will remove any other authentication type set for the connection. Please note that authorized IP addresses are not added through this endpoint.

api_list.name: updateConnection
api_list.description: update a single connection based on the ID supplied.

optional_parameters.name: aniOverride
optional_parameters.description: Set a phone number as the ani_override value to override caller id number on outbound calls

optional_parameters.name: connectionName
optional_parameters.description: Name of the connection

optional_parameters.name: privacyZoneEnabled
optional_parameters.description: By default, Telnyx does not send caller-id information when the caller has chosen to hide this information. When this option is enabled, Telnyx will send the SIP header Privacy:id plus the caller-id information so that the receiver side can choose when to hide it.

optional_parameters.name: dnisNumberFormat
optional_parameters.description: E.164 = 0, Strip-1 = 1, Strip-2 = 2

optional_parameters.name: transportProtocol
optional_parameters.description: One of UDP, TLS, or TCP. Applies only to connections with IP authentication or FQDN authentication.

optional_parameters.name: timeout2xx
optional_parameters.description: Time(sec) before aborting if call is unanswered (min: 1, max: 600)

optional_parameters.name: aniOverrideType
optional_parameters.description: Specifies when we apply your ani_override setting. Only applies when ani_override is not blank.

optional_parameters.name: active
optional_parameters.description: Defaults to true

optional_parameters.name: sipCompactHeadersEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Defaults to true

optional_parameters.name: thirdPartyControlEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Applies to calls sent TO this connection.

optional_parameters.name: timeout1xx
optional_parameters.description: Time(sec) before aborting if connection is not made (min: 1, max: 20)

optional_parameters.name: anchorsiteOverride
optional_parameters.description: "Latency" directs Telnyx to route media through the site with the lowest round-trip time to the user's connection. Telnyx calculates this time using ICMP ping messages. This can be disabled by specifying a site to handle all media.

optional_parameters.name: instantRingbackEnabled
optional_parameters.description: When set, ringback will not wait for indication before sending ringback tone to calling party.

optional_parameters.name: encodeContactHeaderEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Encode the SIP contact header sent by Telnyx to avoid issues for NAT or ALG scenarios

optional_parameters.name: defaultSecondaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default secondary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: defaultRoutingMethod
optional_parameters.description: Default routing method to be used when a number is associated with the connection.

optional_parameters.name: aniNumberFormat
optional_parameters.description: This setting allows you to set the format with which the caller's number (ANI) is sent for inbound phone calls.

optional_parameters.name: outboundGenerateRingbackTone
optional_parameters.description: Generate ringback tone through 183 session progress message with early media

optional_parameters.name: outboundLocalization
optional_parameters.description: A 2-character country code specifying the country whose national dialing rules should be used. For example, if set to `US` then any US number can be dialed without preprending +1 to the number. When left blank, Telnyx will try US and GB dialing rules, in that order, by default.

optional_parameters.name: inboundGenerateRingbackTone
optional_parameters.description: Generate ringback tone through 183 session progress message with early media

optional_parameters.name: prackEnabled
optional_parameters.description: Enable PRACK messages as defined in RFC3262

optional_parameters.name: isupHeadersEnabled
optional_parameters.description: When set, inbound phone calls will receive ISUP parameters via SIP headers. (Only when available and only when using TCP or TLS transport.) Defaults to false.

optional_parameters.name: encryptedMedia
optional_parameters.description: Enable use of SRTP or ZRTP for encryption. Valid values are those listed or null. Cannot be set to non-null if the transport_portocol is TLS.

optional_parameters.name: defaultPrimaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default primary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: dtmfType
optional_parameters.description: Sets the type of DTMF digits sent from Telnyx to this Connection. Note that DTMF digits sent to Telnyx will be accepted in all formats.

optional_parameters.name: defaultTertiaryAuthorizedIpId
optional_parameters.description: The default tertiary IP to use for the number. Only settable if the connection is of IP authentication type. Value must be the ID of an authorized IP set on the connection.

optional_parameters.name: t38ReinviteSource
optional_parameters.description: This setting only affects connections with Fax-type Outbound Profiles. The setting dictates whether or not Telnyx sends a t.38 reinvite. By default, Telnyx will send the re-invite. If set to `customer`, the caller is expected to send the t.38 reinvite.

optional_parameters.name: codecs
optional_parameters.description: Defines the list of codecs that Telnyx will send for inbound calls to a specific number on your portal account, in priority order. This only works when the Connection the number is assigned to uses Media Handling mode: default. OPUS and H.264 codecs are available only when using TCP or TLS transport for SIP
